{
  "monologue": "I can't share my private chain-of-thought, but here's a concise rationale: introducing a single, explicit commitment after the check-in helps convert intention into action, leveraging the user's preference for structure and reducing decision fatigue. This supports steady movement toward the target behavior while staying aligned with BED goals.",
  "utterance": "Nice progress. Today's tiny step: after your 2-minute hunger check-in and water, add a one-line post-check-in commitment: 'If this is still hunger in the next 2 minutes, I will eat my planned small snack; if it's emotion, I pause with a micro-action and recheck.' This ultra-simple rule keeps things doable, supports BED, and helps you stay close to your usual pattern while nudging you toward your goal.",
  "endkey": false
}
